expression: "command_help(\"check\")"
---
Type check Vue SFC files

Usage: check [OPTIONS] [PATTERNS]...

Arguments:
  [PATTERNS]...
          Files or directories to type-check (`.vue`, `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.d.ts`). When omitted, `tsconfig.json` include/exclude/files are used if available

Options:
  -c, --config <CONFIG>
          Config file path

      --no-config
          Do not load a config file

  -s, --socket <SOCKET>
          Connect to check-server via Unix socket (faster for repeated checks, Unix only)

      --tsconfig <TSCONFIG>
          tsconfig.json path

  -f, --format <FORMAT>
          Output format (text, json)

          [default: text]

      --show-virtual-ts
          Show generated virtual TypeScript

      --save-virtual-ts-for <FILE>
          Save generated virtual TypeScript for a file next to that file. Repeatable: pass the flag multiple times to save several files in one run. Pass `__vize_helpers.d.ts` to save the shared helpers preamble file

      --max-warnings <MAX_WARNINGS>
          Maximum number of warnings before failing

      --no-check-props
          Disable prop type checks where supported

      --no-check-emits
          Disable emit type checks where supported

      --no-check-template-bindings
          Disable template binding checks where supported

  -q, --quiet
          Quiet mode - only show summary

      --profile
          Profile mode - output Virtual TS and timing to node_modules/.vize directory

      --corsa-path <CORSA_PATH>
          Path to the Corsa executable (can also use `CORSA_PATH`)

      --servers <SERVERS>
          Number of parallel Corsa servers to use (defaults to an auto-tuned value)

      --declaration
          Emit `.d.ts` files using the materialized Corsa project

      --declaration-dir <DECLARATION_DIR>
          Output directory for emitted `.d.ts` files

  -h, --help
          Print help
